
User Management:-
Super User(Root User):-User is the moast powerful User. HE is the Administater. Ex:-Root, Home Directory:-/root, Shell:-/bash/bin
System User:-Users created by the Softwares and Applications.Created for services or background processes (like mysql, www-data) Ex:-ftp/ssh/apache, Home Directory:-/var/ftp, Shell:-/sbin/nologin
Normal User:-Normal Users are the Users created by the Root User. Ex:-visitor,ec2-User, Home Directory:-/home/username, Shell:-/bash/bin
User:-	A person or process that uses the system (e.g., root, john, ubuntu)
Group:- A collection of users with similar permissions

User Creation:-
Whenevr a user is created in Linux, These things happen by default
1.A home directory is created (/home/username)
2.A UniquemID(UID) and GroupID(GID) are given to user
3.An entry in /etc/passwd

Syntax for creating user in Linux:
--> useradd <option> <username>
1.-u user id
2.-G Secondary group id
3.-g Primary group id
4.-d home directory
5.-c Comment
6.-s Shell
7.init 6 --> is restart the system
8.sudo useradd -m john :- here create a john User in a root User

Software Managenment:-
yum is the primary tool for getting,updating,installing,querying and managing software packages in Linux.
We can use this yum in Red-hat linux distribution only.
1.yum install <package name>
2.yum remove <package name>
3.yum update <package name>
4.yum info <package name>
5.yum list available
6.yum list installed
